The paper deals with building computational models for narratives and evaluating narrative quality, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses active learning and neural networks, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI and cs.LG). The paper also deals with predicting upvotes, which is a form of social network analysis (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves text classification and information retrieval, which are relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
